Encapsulation in Java is a mechanism of wrapping the data (variables) and code acting on the data (methods) together as a single unit

Steps to achieve Encapsulation:
1. Declare the variables of class as private
2. Provide public setter and getter methods to modify and view the variable values

class Employee{

    private int empid;              //private variable
    
    public void setEmpid(int eid){  //public setter method
        this.empid = eid;
    }
    public int getEmpid(){          //public getter method
        return empid;
    }
}
class Company{
    public static void main (String[] args) {
        Employee e = new Employee();
        e.setEmpid(101);
        System.out.println(e.getEmpid());
    }
    
}

o/p:
101
